properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 20 at 3:02PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood
Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin...

Oconto River near Gillett affecting Shawano and Oconto Counties.

.An ice jam will cause water to infiltrate the lowlands along the
river.

The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a

* Flood Warning for
the Oconto River near Gillett.
* From this afternoon until further notice.
* At 2:00 PM CST Thursday the stage was 7.5 feet.
* Flood stage is 7.5 feet.
* Minor flooding is occurring.
* Forecast...No forecast is available for this location.
* Impact...At 7.5 feet, there is widespread flooding of lowland and
agricultural land. Water spreads into Sportsmans Park in the town
of Pulcifer. Water approaches homes downstream of the gauge
southwest of Gillett.
properties.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/grb

The next statement will be issued this evening by 1000 PM CST.
